# Config / secrets (F-22)
# Catch-all for env files anywhere in the tree -- a developer who copies
# deploy/example.env to deploy/.env, web/.env, or config.env will have
# the copy ignored. The canonical example file is the only allowlisted
# entry; if you add another committed example, allowlist it here too.
**/*.env
!deploy/example.env
